I"Z<p>In general, Occam’s razor is a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/technical-indicators-are-heuristics-for-stock-market-forecasting">heuristic</a> for <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/iterated-pruning-is-a-light-weight-approach-to-nudging-text-generation">pruning</a> a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/candidate-solution-overload-is-a-problem">set of candidate solutions</a> to a certain <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/creativity-is-based-on-search-not-generation">search problem</a>. Concretely, when trying to approximate a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/boltzmann-distribution-links-macrostates-with-microstate-probabilities">natural phenomenon</a> with a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/finite-state-dynamical-systems-are-diverse">dynamical system</a>, Occam’s razor is used to select the minimal system which <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neural-manifold-folding-explains-explanatory-drive">explains</a> a certain <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/mindfulness-breaks-self-induced-behaviors">behavior</a>.</p>
